{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, our critic's pariwise comparison setup allows for a single-elimination tournament with the critic as the judge (see Algorithm 3), enabling further policy improvements with additional rollouts.",
    "As shown in Figure 2 (and detailed in Table 8), increasing the number of rollouts from 1 to 16 consistently improves performance.",
    "Notably, with 16 rollouts, RARO achieves 53.6% on the 1.5B model and 57.9% on the 3B model.",
    "When comparing against the RLVR baseline with the same TTS strategy (Table 9), we observe that RARO achieves a similar rate of improvement.",
    "This result highlights that RARO, when combined with test-time search, can scale effectively, matching the scaling trends of models trained with oracle verifiers."
  ]
}